description:
Which Way is Modi’s India Headed? Call me a hopeless romantic (or just a student of political history) But despite the dire situation that India is facing today - I am confident that we will emerge from this crisis as well …. 
Indians have had dictators for lunch before and my core point at the 
@OxfordUnion
 debate was that no one person can alter the destiny of this great nation. They may try, but in the larger scheme of things - we are still on the track we set out in 1947. (Perhaps that’s why this election is even more important)
PS -
It’s not ‘Modi’s India’, just like it was never ‘Indira’s India’.

What the Oxford Union Debate here - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=swSfu0eWzQk&t=8s
